# FastyGoUI ‚Äî composition & ui8px (prototype layer)

## What this phase is (and what it is **not**)

- **Prototype / ‚Äústrength of structure‚Äù:** wireframes and **carcass** UI only‚Äî**no visual design**, no decoration, no brand polish. Goal: correct **information architecture**, **HTML5 semantics**, **accessibility**, and **composition**.
- **Not production:** **`github.com/fastygo/ui8kit`** is **not** a finished product design system or ‚Äúenterprise UI‚Äù. Treat it as a **raw prototype kit**: primitives and composites built from **Tailwind only** (under **ui8px** policy) plus **design tokens in the shadcn style** (e.g. `tweakcn` / semantic color tokens such as `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`). There is **no** separate mandatory kit CSS layer of semantic component classes in this story‚Äî**self-contained** markup + utilities + tokens should be enough to run (including **CDN Tailwind + tweakcn** for quick onboarding).
- **Onboarding:** **repeated utility chains** in component code are **acceptable** here: they stay **transparent** (‚Äúwhat you see is what styles‚Äù) and easy for newcomers. **ui8px** limits **which** utilities appear and keeps **per-line** discipline (see policy); it does **not** mean ‚Äúhide everything behind Go helpers.‚Äù **`class={ ‚Ä¶ }`**, **`Cn`**, and small Go fragments are **optional** optimizations, not the default requirement for every surface.

## Tailwind / ui8px

- Use **only** utilities that pass **`FastyGoUI/.ui8px/policy`** (`allowed.json`, `denied.json`, `groups.json`, `patterns.json`, `scopes.json`). Treat that directory as the **contract** for the prototype utility set.
- After edits to `.templ`, `.css` (where linted), or Go class strings used as classes, run **`bun run lint:ui8px`** and fix violations.
- Prefer **explicit Tailwind lists** on primitives for wireframe-grade surfaces; use **Go helpers / `Cn`** when they genuinely shorten noise **without** hiding required structure for reviewers.

## No raw markup

- **Forbidden:** raw layout/content tags (`div`, `span`, `section`, ‚Ä¶) in app composition. UI comes from **Base** / **UI8Kit** primitives and composites.
- **Mandatory:** **`github.com/fastygo/base`** for the right tag and content model (`block`, `box`, `text`, `stack`, `group`, `table`, `form`, `field`, ‚Ä¶). Check **`github.com/fastygo/base/utils/tags.go`** before choosing semantics.
- **Exception ‚Äî document shell only:** `link`, `script`, `meta`, etc. live in **head** partials (e.g. `internal/views/partials/shell_head.templ`), per UI8Kit shell ownership‚Äînot in body composition.

## Atomic stack

- **Atoms:** `github.com/fastygo/base/*` (+ Base `utils` for tags/Cn/ARIA where applicable).
- **Molecules (UI8Kit primitives ‚Äî mandatory import shape):** **`import "github.com/fastygo/ui8kit/ui"`** (facade only). In **`.templ`**, call primitives as **`@ui.Stack`**, **`@ui.Button`**, **`@ui.Box`**, **`@ui.Text`**, **`@ui.Title`**, ‚Ä¶ using **`ui.StackProps`**, **`ui.ButtonProps`**, etc. Do **not** import granular paths such as `ui8kit/ui/stack` or `ui8kit/ui/button` in this repo unless a maintainer explicitly drops this rule for an edge case.
- **Organisms (UI8Kit composites ‚Äî mandatory import shape):** **`import cmp "github.com/fastygo/ui8kit/components"`**. In **`.templ`**, use **`@cmp.Card`**, **`@cmp.Dialog`**, **`@cmp.Accordion`**, ‚Ä¶ (`cmp.CardProps`, `cmp.ComboboxProps`, ‚Ä¶).
- **Prefer** organism ‚Üí molecule ‚Üí atom. Gaps are filled with **lower layers**, never with raw HTML.
- **In-app registry:** composed pieces belong under **`internal/ui/components`**, **`blocks`**, **`widgets`**, **`layout`** (see **`fastygo-ui-design-system-registry.mdc`**)‚Äîthere is **no** `internal/ui/elements` layer. **`components`** = pure UI; **`widgets`** = UI + logic/API (same rule file).

### UI8Kit imports ‚Äî example (`.templ`)

Use exactly these import lines and call sites:

```go
import "github.com/fastygo/ui8kit/ui"
import cmp "github.com/fastygo/ui8kit/components"

// @ui.Stack(ui.StackProps{ ... }) { ‚Ä¶ }
// @cmp.Card(cmp.CardProps{ ... }) { ‚Ä¶ }
```

**`.go`** helpers that return kit markup should use the same **`ui`** / **`cmp`** packages (`ui.Button`, ‚Ä¶) instead of deep **`ui8kit/ui/‚Ä¶`** paths unless a maintainer documents an exception.

## Semantics (UI8Kit + Base)

- Follow **`@UI8Kit/.cursor/rules/ui8kit-layer.mdc`** and **`@UI8Kit/.cursor/rules/ui8kit-block-box-semantics.mdc`** (Block vs Box, landmarks, nesting, head vs body).
- **`base/block`:** top-level sections/anchors only; **do not nest Block in Block**. Internally use **stack**, **group**, **grid**, **container**, owned table/list/form primitives, or **`base/box`** for neutral layout.

## This repo vs future ‚Äúdesigned‚Äù apps

- **Here (prototype):** styling is **utilities + tokens** in source (templ/Go); avoid shipping a parallel **semantic CSS** story in this repo (no kit-owned `@apply` stacks as the source of truth for chrome). Optional **generated** or **app-level** semantics are a **separate** long-term concern‚Äînot assumed here.
- **Later, per product:** a **consumer app** may add brand layers, **`@apply`**, CLI-driven blocks, or premium tooling that collapses chains into named classes‚Äîthat is **out of scope** for this repository; this repo stays a **neutral structural baseline** built from **Tailwind + ui8px + tokens**.

## Base helpers (use when they help; not mandatory for every class list)

- **`utils/cn.go`** ‚Äî optional class composition.
- **`utils/aria.go`** ‚Äî ARIA for interactive/stateful UI wherever helpers apply (still required where relevant).

For the **JS behavior layer**, **`@ui8kit/aria`**, manifest alignment, **`bun run validate:aria`**, **`bun run test:e2e`** (axe), and **Nu HTML** snapshots, see **`fastygo-ui-validation-testing.mdc`** (and **`fastygo-ui-aria.mdc`** for policy).

On conflict between kit docs and **this** repo‚Äôs prototype rules, prefer **this file** for FastyGoUI: **ui8px gate**, **no raw tags**, **UI8Kit = wireframe Tailwind + tokens (not production DS)**, **explicit utility chains are OK** for onboarding.
